===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|lether|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|leþer||leather|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*leþrą||leather}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*letrom||leather}}. Cognate with West Frisian {{term|leare||leather|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|leder|lang=nl}}, {{term|leer||leather|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Leder||leather|lang=de}}, Swedish {{term|läder||leather|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|leður||leather|lang=is}}. The Celtic forms ({{etyl|cy|-}} {{term|lledr|lang=cy}}, {{etyl|ga|-}} {{term|lethar|lang=ga}}) ultimately derive from the Germanic.

